    "_scoring_notes": "Scoring Procedure and InterpretationThe 46 items of the Stimulant Effect Expectancy Questionnaire (SEEQ) comprise the following 5 scales (Aarons et al., 2001):(1) Global Positive Effects: items 2, 10, 22, 23, 25, 28, 37, 44, 45, and 46(2) Global Negative Effects: items 3, 8, 9, 27, 29, 32, 33, 34, 35, 36, 38, 39, 40, and 43(3) General Arousal: items 6, 12, 14, 15, 17, 20, 21, and 42(4) Anxiety: items 1, 4, 5, 13, 16, 18, 19, and 41(5) Relaxation and Tension Reduction: items 7, 11, 24, and 31The score for each scale is calculated by averaging the item scores, i.e., totaling the item scores and dividing by the number of items in the scale. Each item is scored on a 1 to 5 scale (Disagree Strongly = 1 and Agree Strongly = 5). Of note, items 26 and 30 are not scored. The scoring scheme reflects factors identified in the original publications. Factor structure may differ in individual studies.",
    "likert_options": {
      "points": 5,
      "min": 1,
      "max": 5,
      "labels": [
        "likert_1",
        "likert_2",
        "likert_3",
        "likert_4",
        "likert_5"
      ]
    }
  },
  "translations": {
    "en": {
      "info_520402": "The following questions contain statements about the effects of stimulants, including cocaine and amphetamines (crystal meth, speed). Read each statement carefully and respond according to your own personal thoughts, feelings, and beliefs about stimulants now. We are interested in what you think about stimulants, regardless of what other people might think.Whether or not you have had actual experiences with stimulants yourself, you are to answer in terms of your beliefs about stimulants. It is important that you respond to every question. There are no right or wrong answers.",
      "which_stimulant_drug_most_experience": "Which stimulant drug do you have the most experience with or knowledge about? (check a box)",
      "which_stimulant_drug_most_experience_opt_1": "COCAINE (including crack)",
      "which_stimulant_drug_most_experience_opt_2": "AMPHETAMINES (including crystal meth and speed)",
      "info2_520402": "Please fill out the following questions according to your beliefs about the stimulant drug you know best. PLEASE BE HONEST. REMEMBER, YOUR ANSWERS ARE CONFIDENTIAL. RESPOND TO THESE ITEMS ACCORDING TO WHAT YOU PERSONNALLY BELIEVE TO BE TRUE ABOUT A MODERATE AMOUNT OF STIMULANTS - HOWEVER YOU DEFINE MODERATE.Check the box which shows how much you agree or disagree with each item:",
      "stimulants_make_me_less_hungry": "Stimulants make me less hungry.",
      "stimulants_increase_my_sex_drive": "Stimulants increase my sex drive.",
      "say_things_dont_mean_stimulants": "I say things that I don't mean when I am on stimulants.",
      "effects_not_similar_to_alcohol": "find the effects of stimulants are not similar to those of alcohol.",
      "anxious_or_tense_stimulants": "I am anxious or tense when I am on stimulants.",
      "stimulants_speed_me_up": "Stimulants speed me up.",
      "stimulants_make_me_feel_dreamy": "Stimulants make me feel dreamy and mellow.",
      "stimulants_make_me_shaky": "Stimulants make me shaky.",
      "get_paranoid_on_stimulants": "I can get paranoid when I am on stimulants.",
      "everything_is_right_stimulants": "When I am on stimulants I feel as though everything is right in the world.",
      "not_impatient_stimulants": "I do not become impatient and agitated when I am on stimulants.",
      "stimulants_make_me_hyper": "Stimulants make me 'hyper' (overactive, over-talkative, etc.).",
      "stimulants_uncomfortable_feeling": "Stimulants give me an uncomfortable feeling inside my stomach.",
      "stimulants_give_rush": "Stimulants give me a 'rush', or a sudden sense of being 'swept away'.",
      "stimulants_increase_activity_level": "Stimulants increase my activity level.",
      "grind_teeth_on_stimulants": "I grind my teeth when I am on stimulants.",
      "stimulants_make_my_heart_faster": "Stimulants make my heart beat faster and cause the blood to rush around inside my body.",
      "numb_on_stimulants": "I become numb on stimulants.",
      "bathroom_more_on_stimulants": "I go to the bathroom more when I am on stimulants.",
      "awake_and_alert_on_stimulants": "I become awake and alert when I am on stimulants.",
      "tingly_feeling_on_stimulants": "I get a tingly feeling when I am on stimulants.",
      "more_capable_on_stimulants": "I am more capable of getting things done when I am on stimulants.",
      "stimulants_make_me_feel_important": "Stimulants make me feel more important.",
      "not_easily_frustrated_on_stimulants": "I am not easily frustrated when I am on stimulants.",
      "stimulants_feel_on_top": "Stimulants make me feel as though I am on top of things.",
      "stimulants_not_dizzy": "Stimulants do not make me light-headed or dizzy.",
      "less_sensitive_on_stimulants": "I am less sensitive to other people when I am on stimulants.",
      "can_do_anything_stimulants": "Stimulants make me feel like I can do anything.",
      "difficulty_focusing_stimulants": "I have difficulty focusing on one thing at a time when I am on stimulants.",
      "stimulants_do_not_make_clear": "Stimulants do not make things seem clear.",
      "stimulants_do_not_make_sweat": "Stimulants do not make me sweat.",
      "after_stimulant_depressed": "After the stimulant 'high' is over, I become depressed or 'burned out'.",
      "stimulants_decrease_my_sexual_performance": "Stimulants decrease my sexual performance.",
      "same_thing_over_stimulants": "Stimulants make me do the same thing over and over again.",
      "never_satisfied_on_stimulants": "I am never satisfied when I am on stimulants - I always want more.",
      "less_aware_on_stimulants": "I am less aware of reality when I am on stimulants.",
      "stimulants_give_sense_of_control": "Stimulants give me a sense of being in control.",
      "stimulants_cause_hallucinations": "Stimulants cause hallucinations.",
      "stimulants_cause_me_lose_interest": "Stimulants cause me to lose interest in what I am doing.",
      "stimulants_make_my_judgment_worse": "Stimulants make my judgment worse.",
      "able_to_drink_more_stimulants": "I am able to drink a lot more without getting drunk when I am on stimulants.",
      "more_talkative_stimulants": "I am more talkative when I am on stimulants.",
      "become_fearful_on_stimulants": "I become fearful on stimulants.",
      "stimulants_make_me_aggressive": "Stimulants make me aggressive and dominating.",
      "parties_more_fun_on_stimulants": "Parties are more fun when I am on stimulants.",
      "stimulants_make_me_happy": "Stimulants make me feel very happy.",
      "likert_1": "DISAGREE STRONGLY",
      "likert_2": "DISAGREE SOMEWHAT",
      "likert_3": "UNCERTAIN",
      "likert_4": "AGREE SOMEWHAT",
      "likert_5": "AGREE STRONGLY"
    }
  }
}
